```julia
function timezone_bumper(dt::DateTime, bump::Integer = 3)
    if !isa(dt, DateTime))
        error("Input must be of type DateTime")
    end

    return dt + hours(bump)
end
```
This function `timezone_bumper` takes a `DateTime` input and an optional `bump` argument (default is 3 hours). It checks if the input is a `DateTime`, throwing an error for `Date` types. Finally, it returns the timestamp incremented by the specified number of hours.
